Here is a complete, structured report of everything you need to build SCRN002.

---

## Full Codebase Analysis for Snippet Manager Screen (SCRN002)

---

### 1. ClipboardHistoryView — `/src/components/clipboard_history/clipboard_history_view.tsx`

This is the canonical pattern to follow. Full content above. Key architectural points:

**Structure:**
- Self-contained component — owns its own `SearchBar`, body layout, `ActionPanel`, `Alert`, and `HUDContainer`
- Renders as an `isFullView` in `App.tsx`, meaning it gets a bare `command-palette__nav-view` wrapper and renders its own `SearchBar` (instead of App.tsx's SearchBar)
- Uses `useNavigation()` from context (read-only, for `nav.breadcrumbs`) — does NOT push/pop itself
- Uses `useHUD`, `useAlert`, `useKeyboardShortcut` hooks internally

**State pattern:**
```ts
const [entries, setEntries] = useState<ClipboardEntry[]>(MOCK_CLIPBOARD_ENTRIES);
const [query, setQuery] = useState('');
const [filterValue, setFilterValue] = useState('all');
const [selectedIndex, setSelectedIndex] = useState(0);
const [actionsOpen, setActionsOpen] = useState(false);
```

**List rendering pattern:**
- `flatItems` = pinnedItems + recentItems
- Uses a `globalIndex` counter across sections to maintain a flat index for `List`
- `<List itemCount={N} onActiveIndexChange={...} onAction={...}>` wraps `<ListSection>` wrapping `<ListItem index={idx} ...>`

**ActionPanel wiring:**
```tsx
<ActionPanel
  contextLabel="Clipboard History"
  actions={[{ label: 'Paste', shortcut: <Kbd keys={['↵']} /> }, ...]}
  dropdownOpen={actionsOpen}
  dropdownSections={dropdownSections}
  onDropdownClose={closeActions}
/>
```

**SCSS:** Minimal — only one class `.clipboard-history__color-dot` for the color swatch inline display.

---

### 2. `clipboard_data.ts` — `/src/data/clipboard_data.ts`

```ts
export interface ClipboardEntry {
  id: string;
  content: string;
  contentType: 'text' | 'link' | 'color' | 'image';
  sourceApp: string;
  sourceIcon: ReactNode;
  copiedAt: Date;
  pinned: boolean;
}
```

Mock data uses `Date.now()` minus offsets for relative timestamps. Icons are sourced from `src/components/icons/icons.tsx` (called as functions, not JSX — e.g., `TerminalIcon()`).

---

### 3. `App.tsx` — `/src/App.tsx`

**Navigation union type:**
```ts
type NavViewData =
  | { type: 'grid' }
  | { type: 'form' }
  | { type: 'clipboard' }
  | { type: 'detail'; item: ListItemData };
```

To add SCRN002 you will need to extend this union with `| { type: 'snippets' }`.

**Navigation push pattern:**
```ts
// In handleDrillIn:
if (item.id === 'clipboard-history') {
  push('Clipboard History', { type: 'clipboard' });
  setQuery('');
  setSelectedIndex(0);
}
```

The `snippets` item already exists in `MOCK_SECTIONS` with `id: 'snippets'`, so the drill-in handler just needs a new branch:
```ts
else if (item.id === 'snippets') {
  push('Snippet Manager', { type: 'snippets' });
  setQuery('');
  setSelectedIndex(0);
}
```

**`isFullView` pattern — what makes ClipboardHistory "take over" the whole palette:**
```ts
const isFullView = viewType === 'clipboard';
```

When `true`:
- App.tsx's `SearchBar` is hidden (hidden via `{!isFullView && <SearchBar .../>}`)
- App.tsx's `ActionPanel` is hidden
- App.tsx's `Alert` is hidden
- App.tsx's `HUDContainer` is hidden
- The view is rendered in a bare `command-palette__nav-view` div (no additional `command-palette__body` wrapper)

`renderCurrentView()` is the switch that maps `entry.data.type` to a component. Add `case 'snippets': return <SnippetManagerView />;` there.

**`CreateSnippetView` already exists in App.tsx** (lines 262–384) — a form-based snippet creator with all fields wired. However, it's private to App.tsx. For SCRN002, it should be extracted to `src/components/snippet_manager/`.

**Existing SnippetFormState + constants in App.tsx:**
```ts
interface SnippetFormState {
  name: string;
  keyword: string;
  snippet: string;
  category: string;
  tags: string[];
  isShared: boolean;
  expiresAt: string;
}

const SNIPPET_TAGS = [
  { label: 'JavaScript', value: 'javascript' },
  { label: 'TypeScript', value: 'typescript' },
  { label: 'Python', value: 'python' },
  { label: 'React', value: 'react' },
  { label: 'CSS', value: 'css' },
  { label: 'HTML', value: 'html' },
  { label: 'Shell', value: 'shell' },
  { label: 'Markdown', value: 'markdown' },
];

const SNIPPET_CATEGORIES = [
  { label: 'General', value: 'general' },
  { label: 'Code', value: 'code' },
  { label: 'Email', value: 'email' },
  { label: 'Template', value: 'template' },
];
```

---

### 4. `types.ts` — `/src/types.ts`

```ts
export interface ListItemData {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  subtitle?: string;
  icon?: ReactNode;
  accessories?: ListItemAccessoryData[];
  detail?: ListItemDetailData;
}

export interface ListItemAccessoryData {
  text?: string;
  icon?: ReactNode;
  date?: Date;
  tag?: { text: string; color?: TagColor; };
  tooltip?: string;
}

export interface ListItemDetailData {
  markdown: string;
  metadata?: ListItemMetadataEntry[];
}

export type ListItemMetadataEntry =
  | { type: 'label'; title: string; text?: string; }
  | { type: 'link'; title: string; text: string; target: string; }
  | { type: 'tag-list'; title: string; tags: { text: string; color?: TagColor; }[]; }
  | { type: 'separator' };

export interface SectionData { title: string; items: ListItemData[]; }
export interface GridItemData { id: string; title: string; subtitle?: string; icon?: ReactNode; }
export interface ColorItemData extends GridItemData { color: string; }
```

You will need to add a `SnippetEntry` type to `types.ts` for the Snippet Manager's data.

---

### 5. Form Components — `/src/components/form/index.ts`

All exports available:
```ts
export { Form }               // from './form'
export { FormCheckbox }       // from './form_checkbox'
export { FormDatePicker }     // from './form_date_picker'
export { FormDropdown }       // from './form_dropdown'
export type { FormDropdownOption }
export { FormFilePicker }     // from './form_file_picker'
export type { FilePickerFile }
export { FormPasswordField }  // from './form_password_field'
export { FormSeparator }      // from './form_separator'
export { FormTagPicker }      // from './form_tag_picker'
export type { FormTagPickerOption }
export { FormTextArea }       // from './form_text_area'
export { FormTextField }      // from './form_text_field'
```

---

### 6. Navigation System — `/src/hooks/use_navigation.ts`

**`useNavigationStack`** (used in App.tsx root) owns the stack state.
**`useNavigation`** (used in child views like ClipboardHistoryView) reads from context.

```ts
export interface NavigationContext<T = unknown> {
  push: (title: string, data: T) => void;
  pop: () => void;
  popToRoot: () => void;
  currentEntry: NavigationEntry<T> | null;
  breadcrumbs: BreadcrumbItem[];
  canGoBack: boolean;
  direction: TransitionDirection;   // 'push' | 'pop' | 'none'
  stackDepth: number;
  navKey: number;
}
```

Breadcrumbs are passed to `SearchBar` as `breadcrumbs={nav.breadcrumbs.length > 0 ? nav.breadcrumbs : undefined}` to show the back navigation path.

---

### Key Implementation Blueprint for SCRN002

**Files to create:**
- `src/data/snippet_data.ts` — `SnippetEntry` interface + `MOCK_SNIPPET_ENTRIES`
- `src/components/snippet_manager/snippet_manager_view.tsx` — main list view (pattern: ClipboardHistoryView)
- `src/components/snippet_manager/snippet_manager_view.scss`
- `src/components/snippet_manager/create_snippet_view.tsx` — extracted from App.tsx's `CreateSnippetView`

**Files to modify:**
- `src/App.tsx` — add `| { type: 'snippets' }` to `NavViewData`, add drill-in branch for `item.id === 'snippets'`, add `case 'snippets'` in `renderCurrentView()`, extend `isFullView` check, remove inline `CreateSnippetView` (or keep it for the `'form'` route and use the new extracted component from snippet_manager)
- `src/types.ts` — add `SnippetEntry` interface

**Navigation wiring summary:**
```
Root list → user selects "Search Snippets" (id: 'snippets') → Enter/↵
→ App.tsx handleDrillIn: push('Snippet Manager', { type: 'snippets' })
→ renderCurrentView() returns <SnippetManagerView />
→ SnippetManagerView renders its own SearchBar, list, ActionPanel
→ "Create Snippet" action → nav.push or internal push to form sub-view
```

**`isFullView` decision:** The Snippet Manager should follow the same pattern as ClipboardHistory — `isFullView` should include `viewType === 'snippets'` so the view owns its own chrome (SearchBar, ActionPanel, HUD, Alert).
